  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-02-28",
    "date": "2022-04-22T18:33:24Z",
    "text": "Emmett Till Antilynching Act\n\nThis bill makes lynching a federal hate crime offense.\n\nSpecifically, the bill imposes criminal penalties\u2014a fine, a prison term of up to 30 years, or both\u2014on an individual who conspires to commit a hate crime offense that results in death or serious bodily injury or that includes kidnapping or an attempt to kidnap, aggravated sexual abuse or an attempt to commit aggravated sexual abuse, or an attempt to kill."
